  01 May 2015; Jeroen Roovers <jer@gentoo.org> fcitx-libpinyin-0.3.1.ebuild:
  Stable for PPC64 (bug #540844).

  19 Apr 2015; Anthony G. Basile <blueness@gentoo.org>
  fcitx-libpinyin-0.2.1.ebuild, fcitx-libpinyin-0.3.1.ebuild:
  Keyword ~ppc and ~ppc64.  Bug #498686.

  03 Feb 2015; Ben de Groot <yngwin@gentoo.org> fcitx-libpinyin-0.3.1.ebuild,
  metadata.xml:
  Fix build failure when Qt4 is not installed (bug 537228). This is made
  optional by toggling the dictmanager USE flag, which requires dev-
  qt/qtwebkit:4.

  01 Jun 2014; Naohiro Aota <naota@gentoo.org> fcitx-libpinyin-0.2.1.ebuild:
  Update libpinyin dependency #504162

  08 Mar 2014; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> fcitx-libpinyin-0.3.1.ebuild:
  amd64 stable, bug 498688

  03 Aug 2013; Agostino Sarubbo <ago@gentoo.org> fcitx-libpinyin-0.2.1.ebuild:
  Stable for ppc, wrt bug #461512

  03 Aug 2013; Agostino Sarubbo <ago@gentoo.org> fcitx-libpinyin-0.2.1.ebuild:
  Stable for x86, wrt bug #461512

  03 Aug 2013; Agostino Sarubbo <ago@gentoo.org> fcitx-libpinyin-0.2.1.ebuild:
  Stable for amd64, wrt bug #461512

*fcitx-libpinyin-0.3.1 (24 Jul 2013)

  24 Jul 2013; Ben de Groot <yngwin@gentoo.org> +fcitx-libpinyin-0.3.1.ebuild:
  Version bump

